description:
&lt;p&gt;Chesterfield Royal Hospital are looking to recruit Registered Nurses into our Surgical Specialties Division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to welcome you to one of three Care Units within our Division where you will have the opportunity to work in one area or build a rotational/development package to enable you to gain a full insight&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surgical Support Services Care Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Encompassing Critical Care, Theatres, Pre-assessment and Day Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integrated Surgical Care Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spanning over several out-patient departments and our two acute surgical wards covering both electives and emergencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Orthopaedic and Specialist Care Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elective and Trauma Orthopaedics, Short Stay Surgery, Breast Care and Urology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All areas are supported with a senior leadership team, a clinical ward matron and a team of band 6 nurses.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We promote career progression via our onsite education centre, clinical skills team, clinical educators and speciality competency booklets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note if you are a final year student and would like to apply please email joanne.cowlishaw@nhs.net or clairedavies4@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Matrons Sam Wain (Integrated Surgical Care Unit), Mandy Marples (Surgical Support Care Unit) and Claire Wells (Orthopaedic and Specialist Care Unit) can be contacted for an informal discussion via switchboard on 01246 277271&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alternatively contact our Nursing Workforce Coordinator or Recruitment Coordinator via email who would be happy to arrange informal visits: clairedavies4@nhs.net / joanne.cowlishaw@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
